definition.value: A Province in southern Algeria.

A Province of Algeria. It is located in the north-west of the country. The province is bordered to the east by the provinces of Mostaganem, to the south east by Mascara, to the south west by Sidi Bel Abbes and to the west by Ain Temouchent.
Not clear that all Districts are added.

A Province in the south-eastern corner of Algeria. It borders Libya to the east, Ouargla Province to the north and, Tamanghasset Province to the east and south.
A province in the east Algeria around 200 km from the capital Algiers.
A Province in northern Algeria, between Algiers and Tizi-Ouzou.

One of the governorates of Egypt. It is the southmost governorate in Upper Egypt. The capital of the governorate is Aswan. It borders Qena Governorate to the north, Red Sea Governorate to the east, New Valley Governorate to the west, and Sudan to the south.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It stretches for about 120 km along the banks of the Nile. The capital of the governorate is the city of Asyut.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the centre of the country.
One of the governorates of Egypt located in the middle of the country.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the center of the country.
One of the governorates of Upper Egypt.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the south of the country, and covers a stretch of the Nile valley. Its capital is the city of Qena.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the south of the country (Upper Egypt), and covers a stretch of the Nile Valley. Its capital is the city of Sohag.
One of the governorates of Egypt, located in the north of the country, lying directly on the Mediterranean Sea.

One of the governorates of Egypt. It is located between the Nile and the Red Sea in the southeast of the country and its southern border forms part of Egypt's border with Sudan. Its capital is Hurghada.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the north of the country.
One of the governorates of Egypt, lying northeast of Cairo.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the north of the country.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is located in the north of the country, south of Kafr el-Sheikh Governorate, and north of Monufia Governorate. Its capital is Tanta.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It lies in the north of the country along the western branch of the Nile. Its capital is the city of Kafr el-Sheikh. It was once part of the Gharbia Governorate.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the north of the country (south of Gharbiyah and north of Cairo) and its capital is Shibin el-Kom.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the north of the country. Its capital is Banha.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the north of the country. Its capital is Zagazig.
One of the governorates of Egypt. Its capital is the national capital of Cairo.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the northeast of the country. Its capital is the city of Ismailia.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the northeast of the country. Its capital is the city of Port Said.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the northeast of the country and is coterminous with the city of Suez. It is situated East of Delta, North of Suez Gulf.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the north-west of the country, bordering Libya. Its capital is Mersa Matruh.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the south-west of the country, between the Nile and Libya. Its capital is the Kharga Oasis.
